\begin{array}{cl}
-x - 3 & \text{if } x \le 1, \\
\frac{x}{2} + 1 & \text{if } x > 1.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find the sum of all values of $x$ such that $f(x) = 0$.

solution:
[asy]
pair D,EE,F,P,Q,G;

G = (0,0);
D = (1.2,0);
P= (-0.6,0);
EE = (0,1.6);
Q = (0,-0.8);
F = 2*Q - D;
draw(P--D--EE--F--D);
draw(EE--Q);
